    "Html": "<p>My team is using the June 2008 release for a WPF desktop application.</p>\r\n<p>Is there a published set of steps to help us to understand the changes we will need to make to update? &nbsp;I see even the core set of namespaces have been expanded.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks in advance for the help!</p>\r\n<p>Tracy</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2009-06-17T12:18:25.267-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
  {
    "Id": "202634",
    "ThreadId": "59856",
    "Html": "<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\"><span style=\"font-size:small\">Hi Tracy,</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-family:Calibri;font-size:small\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\"><span style=\"font-size:small\">The following article from the Prism-v2 documentation contains the breaking changes between Prism-v1 and Prism-v2</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-indent:-18pt;margin:0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:small\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font:7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><a href=\"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dd490816.aspx\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri;font-size:small\">Upgrading from the Composite Application Guidance for WPF - June 2008</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-family:Calibri;font-size:small\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">If you do not mind, I will briefly share my own experience migrating from Prism-v1 to Prism-v2. Most of the changes we performed to the code were pretty quick, and we were able to get the application running really fast.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">However, we spent some time with the Unit Tests with some considerable changes in the Region/Region manager mocks, which might have been faster if we&rsquo;d have used a mocking framework in the first place.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-family:Calibri;font-size:small\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">I hope this helps.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt -0.6pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-family:Calibri;font-size:small\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt -0.6pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Damian Schenkelman</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/dschenkelman\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri;font-size:small\">http://blogs.southworks.net/dschenkelman</span></a></span></p>",
